This paper is about 3D shape reconstruction from 2D images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and deep learning (cs.LG) communities. The proposed framework involves camera pose estimation, which is related to graphics (cs.GR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of semi-supervised learning, which is a common technique in robotics (cs.RO) where labeled data may be scarce. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.GR, cs.AI, and cs.RO.
